The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, Nov. 21: Four officials of a small IT company, Cyndrake Solutions, in Salt Lake were arrested today following complaints of fraud by some of its employees.     
	Sourav Mitra and Soumen Chattopadhyay, both directors of the company, and Bhaskar Dalapati and Pinaki Sengupta, their accomplices who also worked in Cyndrake, were arrested in their office. Employees said the firm had paid them lesser than what they were promised and had not returned the Rs 60,000 they had paid as a bond that they were supposed to get back after a year.        
	Calcutta: The family of a Delhi University professor from Bengal who found hanging in his staff quarters on November 17 has asked for a probe into his death. Anuradha, the sister of Achyut Mandal who was a student of Presidency College, has lodged a police complaint in Delhi. She said the room where Achyut was found hanging had a low ceiling and the few people who saw the body said his feet were touching the ground.        
	Calcutta: Part of a godown at the Hooghly Jute Mill in Garden Reach was gutted in a fire. There were no casualties.         
	Chinsurah: The superintendent of Chinsurah sadar hospital was assaulted by relatives of a woman who died allegedly because of medical negligence. Papiya Ghosh, 23, of Taldanga, was admitted to the hospital on Friday night with abdominal pain. She died the following morning. Her relatives alleged that the doctors had administered wrong medicine that led to her death.                                                                                                                                                      
